body:
**Nit** [CRF-4] The doc comment describes only the happy path (`readErr` received, error discarded). It says nothing about the timeout branch on line 185 that returns `"timeout waiting for read to finish after close"`. A reader of the doc without the body would conclude `forceClose` always returns nil.

Suggestion:
```go
// forceClose closes the underlying connection and waits for the read to
// unblock. The read error is caused by the close, so it is expected and
// discarded. Returns an error if the read does not unblock within
// readWaitTimeout.
```
*(Leorio)*

> 🤖

